    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>A heavy brass bombard is perched atop the wall, pointing out to sea.

From here, you have a commanding view of the flooded fortress.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Leave the bombard alone.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>The bombard continues its lonely vigil.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Load the bombard.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>Carefully, you ease the shell into the bombard.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You know that swell of fatherly pride when you see a newborn?

"Getting my taste of it." 

Maia pats the hide of the weapon. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText>"You know that swell of motherly pride when you see a newborn?

"Getting my taste of it." 

Maia pats the hide of the weapon. </FemaleText>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Turn the bombard toward the cluster of nāga.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>45</ID>
      <DefaultText>You light the fuse and plug your ears.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>46</ID>
      <DefaultText>Carefully, you ease the shell into the bombard.

It's now loaded and pointed toward the sea.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>56</ID>
      <DefaultText>The gears at its base are rusted stuck. It will take some kind of lubricating oil - or an incredible amount of force - to move the platform.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>57</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Fire the bombard.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>63</ID>
      <DefaultText>You try, but it's stuck.

Looking down, you notice the gears attached to the rotating platform are rusted.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>65</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Push the bombard into position.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>66</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Push the bombard into position.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>67</ID>
      <DefaultText>You push.

Despite the rusted platform's shrieks and the burn in your own arms and legs, you manage to turn the bombard toward the nāga.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>68</ID>
      <DefaultText>You push, but the bombard hardly moves.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>69</ID>
