    <Entry>
      <ID>73</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Step back from the rotating platform.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>82</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Aim the bombard at the cluster of nāga.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>83</ID>
      <DefaultText>You consult the artillery manual you found and use it to line up your shot.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>84</ID>
      <DefaultText>You consider your target and ratchet the bombard back to what looks like a reasonable angle.

Probably.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>85</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Captain? All due respect, but we'll make it out of here faster without a gaping hole in our ship." 

Maia bites her lower lip and squints to adjust the aim.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>87</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Whoever was shirking their maintenance duty had better be among the casualties." 

Maia glowers at the sorry state of the platform.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>92</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Rub cooking fat into the gears.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>93</ID>
      <DefaultText>It's messy and smelly work, but once the gears - and your arms - are liberally greased, you're able to turn the bombard.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>96</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Scan the fortress.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>97</ID>
      <DefaultText>Broken towers rise feebly from the water, and corpses and debris float between them.

You see no sign of life until you note movement near the center of the fort.

A large cluster of nāga has congregated on the central walkway.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>98</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Aim the bombard using the artillery manual as a guide.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>99</ID>
      <DefaultText>You adjust the bombard's angle to account for the proper trajectory.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>101</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Check for ammunition.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>102</ID>
      <DefaultText>The bombard itself is not loaded, and you don't see any ammunition for it nearby.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>103</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Examine the rotating platform.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>104</ID>
      <DefaultText>You push, but the bombard hardly moves.

Nevertheless, the effort is so taxing that you wrench your shoulder.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>105</ID>
      <DefaultText>You push, but the bombard hardly moves.

Nevertheless, the effort is so taxing that you wrench your shoulder.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>106</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Specified 0] pushes, but the bombard hardly moves.

Nevertheless, the strain wrenches [Specified 0]'s shoulder.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>107</ID>
      <DefaultText>You estimate the distance to the nāga and consider what you know about ballistics and parabolic trajectories.

After a few mental calculations, you ratchet the bombard into a suitable firing position. You're confident you can take out the nāga on the platform at this angle.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>108</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Didn't even have to count on your fingers. Very impressive, captain." 

Maia pats your shoulder.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>110</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Best pay another visit to the anxious quartermaster if we're low on shot." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>112</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Perhaps one of those survivors in the storage tower could help us," Aloth says.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>113</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If anybody knows how to load this thing, it'd be that nervous lady."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>114</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Certainly the survivors must know where ammunition for this beast is stored."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>115</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Might be the blue lass from Rauatai knows where we can scrounge ourselves up some big honking balls for this beast."

Serafen glances towards the tower. 
</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
